    rdfs:label "CRF sector (IPCC 2006): maritime navigation"@en ;
    ns1:IAO_0000115 "The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'maritime navigation' is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories. Emissions from fuels used by vessels of all flags that are engaged in international water-borne navigation. The international navigation may take place at sea, on inland lakes and waterways and in coastal waters. It includes emissions from journeys that depart in one country and arrive in a different country. It excludes consumption by fishing vessels." ;
